Part 1:

nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % mkdir first
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % cd first
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % touch person.txt
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % mv person.txt another.txt
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cp another.txt copy.txt
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % rm copy.txt
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cp first second
cp: first: No such file or directory
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cp -f first second
cp: first: No such file or directory
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cp -r first second
cp: first: No such file or directory
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cp -R first second
cp: first: No such file or directory
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air first % cd ..
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % cp -R first second
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % rmdir second
rmdir: second: Directory not empty
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % rmdir -rf second
rmdir: illegal option -- r
usage: rmdir [-pv] directory ...
nickbutani@Nicks-MacBook-Air ~ % rm -r second


Part 2:

1. What does the man command do? Type in man rm. How do you scroll and get out?
A- man command used to display user manual of whatever command user want to use. You can use S, down errow or mouse to scroll down and use Q to get out.

2. Look at the man page for ls. What does the -l flag do? What does the -a flag do?
A- When -l flag used it will list files in long formate. When -a flag used it will include directory entries whose name begin with ('.').

3. How do you jump between words in the terminal?
A- You can jump between the words in the terminal by using Option/Alt + left/right.

4. How do you get to the end of a line in terminal?
A- You can get to end if the line using Command + e shortcut.

5. How do you move your cursor to the beginning in terminal?
A- You can use Command + a to move cursor to the beginning.

6. How do you delete a word (without pressing backspace multiple times) in terminal?
A- You can use Command + w to delete the word. 

7. What is the difference between a terminal and shell?
A- a terminal is a program that provides a user interface, a shell is a command-line interpreter that processes commands.

8. What is an absolute path?
A- Path that start from root directory and give complete location of file.

9. What is an relative path?
A- Path that start a current location.

10. What is a flag? Give three examples of flags you have used.
A- Flag gives additional support to execute the command. I have used -r with rm command and cp command. -a and -l for the ls command.

11. What do the r and f flags do with the rm command?
A- r flag attempt to remove the file hierarchy rooted in each file argument. f flag attempt to remove the files without prompting for confirmation, regardless of the file's permissions.
